Global Burden of osteoarthritis associated with high body mass index in 204 
countries and territories, 1990-2019: findings from the Global Burden of Disease 
Study 2019.

Zhao G(1), Zhu S(2), Zhang F(2), Zhang X(1), Zhang X(2), Li T(2), Li D(3), Zhu 
W(4).

Author information:
(1)Department of Public Health, School of Public Health, Wuhan University, 
430071, Wuhan, China.
(2)Department of Occupational and Environmental Health, School of Public Health, 
Wuhan University, 430071, Wuhan, China.
(3)Department of Occupational and Environmental Health, School of Public Health, 
Wuhan University, 430071, Wuhan, China. djli@whu.edu.cn.
(4)Department of Occupational and Environmental Health, School of Public Health, 
Wuhan University, 430071, Wuhan, China. weizhu@whu.edu.cn.

OBJECTIVE: To quantify the burden of osteoarthritis (OA) associated with high 
body mass index (BMI) across 204 countries and territories from 1990 to 2019.
METHODS: This study extracted global, regional, and national data on years lived 
with disability (YLD) of OA associated with high BMI from GBD 2019. The YLD 
burden of OA associated with high BMI was systematically analyzed by age, SDI, 
sex, and EAPC.
